article.description: Mike Hughes scored 18 points, Jake Allsmiller added 17 and Georgia Southern routed Arkansas State 90-59 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Georgia Southern routs Arkansas State 90-59
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. -- Mike Hughes scored 18 points, Jake Allsmiller added 17 and Georgia Southern routed Arkansas State 90-59 on Thursday night. Tookie Brown had 15 points, and Ike Smith and Montae Glenn chipped in 10 apiece for Georgia State (13-11, 6-9 Sun Belt Conference), which bounced back from an 80-76 loss at South Alabama on Feb. 13 that had snapped a four-game winning streak. Devin Carter made five 3-pointers and finished with 22 points on 8-of-17 shooting from the field to lead Arkansas State (11-15, 7-8), which has lost four straight. Georgia Southern had a double-digit lead midway through the first half and built a 49-22 halftime lead. Allsmiller made five 3-pointers and Hughes had 10 points in the first half. Hughes made a 3-pointer and the Eagles had a 39-point lead with 16 minutes left.
